(1+\dfrac{1}{n})^n>2
\forall n \in \mathbb N, n>1
(1+\dfrac{1}{n})^n<3, \forall n \in \mathbb N
(1+\frac{1}{n})^n=1+n(\frac{1}{n})+\frac{n(n-1)}{1\cdot 2}(\frac{1}{n})^2+\frac{n(n-1)(n-3)}{1\cdot 2\cdot 3}(\frac{1}{n})^3+\cdots \frac{n(n-1)\cdots 2\cdot 1}{n!}(\frac{1}{n})^2=1+1+(1-\frac{1}{n})\frac{1}{2!}+(1-\frac{1}{n})(1-\frac{2}{n})\frac{1}{3!}+\cdots+(1-\frac{1}{n})(1-\frac{2}{n})\cdots (1-\frac{n-1}{n})\frac{1}{n!}
n\neq 1
(1+\frac{1}{n})^n>2
(1-\frac{1}{n}), (1-\frac{2}{n}),...
1
(1-\frac{1}{n}), (1-\frac{2}{n}),...
(1+\frac{1}{n})^n<2+\frac{1}{2!}+\frac{1}{3!}+\cdots +\frac{1}{n!}
\frac{1}{n!}<\frac{1}{2^{n-1}}
<2+\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2^2}+\cdots +\frac{1}{2^{n-1}}<3
